[1] Peru, Cusco, Paucartambo
Date: Fri 19 Oct 2018
Source: RPP [edited]
https://rpp.pe/peru/cusco/nino-de-un-ano-es-la-cuarta-victima-de-sarampion-en-cusco-noticia-1157759


There are 4 children under age 5 who are new measles victims after the outbreak in Cusco.

Pablo Grajeda, head of the Bureau of Health Intelligence Directorate Cusco Regional Health (Diresa) said that the child has high fever and rashes on various parts of his body, so we proceeded to perform scrub with vaccination in the area.

So far this year [2018] at least 76 suspected measles cases were recorded throughout the Cusco region. Analyzes are sent to Lima for confirmation or to rule out a case; the results usually come up in 3 weeks, said the doctor.

Four weeks ago, DIRESA Cusco asked the Ministry of Health (MoH), to declare a health emergency for an outbreak of measles; however, the request has not been answered. At this time, there are only vaccines for children under 5 years.

