[2] Canada (Manitoba): travel associated and contact
Date: Mon 22 Oct 2018
Source: Global News [excerpted, edited]
https://globalnews.ca/news/4580925/two-measles-cases-confirmed-in-manitoba-including-baby/


The province confirmed on Mon 22 Oct 2018 that 2 cases of measles have been reported in Manitoba.

According to Manitoba's chief provincial public health officer, both people affected live in the Interlake Eastern Regional Health Authority and are recovering at home.

The 1st case, a child under the age of one, is believed to have contracted the measles virus out of the country. The 2nd case is a close contact of the child.

Public health officials have identified everyone in contact with the subjects and are continuing to monitor the situation.

[Byline: Sam Thompson]

