[3] Europe: record high number of cases
Date: Sun 21 Oct 2018
Source: WILX [edited]
https://www.wilx.com/content/news/Measles-at-record-high-in-Europe-498138521.html


Measles is sparking new concern after years of decline.

In the U.S., the CDC has confirmed 137 cases in 24 states and the District of Columbia. In Europe, measles cases have reached a record high.

Top health officials at the European Commission tell NBC News the root of the problem is plummeting vaccination rates sparked by a different kind of contagion, the growing anti-vaccine movement.

"It's the main factor leading to the outbreaks. it's unacceptable to have in the 21st century diseases that should have been and could have been eradicated," said Anca Paduraru with the European Commission.

A similar trend is now playing out in the U.S., where the CDC warns that the number of children not getting vaccinated is growing.

