[5] Uganda: refugee settlements
Date: Fri 19 Oct 2018
Source: Relief web [edited]
https://reliefweb.int/report/uganda/measles-outbreak-analysis-refugee-settlements-uganda-sept-2018


Outbreaks have been experienced in Nakivale, Oruchinga, Kiryandongo, Rwamwanja, Kyaka II and Kyangwali refugee settlements.

Kyangwali has so far registered 29 cases of measles, of which 48% are refugees and 52% host population, 55% male and 45% female, and 90% are above 9 months of age, 7% between 6 to 9 months of age, and 3% below 6 months.

Rwamwanja registered a total of 189 cases so far, of which 53% are male and 47% female, 56% refugees, and 44% host population, and 74% of the cases were above 9 months of age, 20% between 6 to 9 months, and 6% were below 6 months of age

Kyaka has so far registered 48 cases of suspected measles, of which 77% are refugees, and 23% are the host population, 44% are male, and 56% female, and 96% of the cases are above 9 months of age, and 4% are between 6 to 9 months of age. No cases for below 6 months registered so far.

Kiryandongo registered 61 cases so far, of which 60% are male and 40% female, 50% refugees and 50% nationals, and 73% of the affected population are adults above 9 months of age, 24% are between 6 to 9 months, and 3% are less than 6 months of age.

No death has been registered in the refugee settlements due to measles ever since the outbreak in January 2018

