[6] Philippines (Central Visayas)
Date: Sun 21 Oct 2018
Source: Cebu Daily News [edited]
https://cebudailynews.inquirer.net/199953/measles-cases-in-cv-increased-by-559


The Department of Health in Central Visayas (DOH-7) has expressed alarm over the sudden increase of measles cases in the region this year [edited].

Ruff Vincent Valdevieso, expanded immunization program coordinator of DOH-7, said that they have recorded at least 290 cases of measles from January to 13 Oct this year [2018]. One person was reportedly dead due to measles.

Valdevieso explained that it is 559% higher compared to the same period last year [2017]. In 2017, only 44 measles cases were recorded.

The sudden increase of cases this year [2018] was attributed to the low turnout of people in availing the free immunization services at local health centers.

[Byline: Futch Anthony Inso]

