[7] Pakistan
Date: Tue 23 Oct 2018
Source: Business Recorder [edited]
https://www.brecorder.com/2018/10/23/448624/measles-campaign-in-sindh-covers-3-65mn-children/


Provincial Minister for Health and Population Welfare Dr Azra Fazal Pechuho on Mon [22 Oct 2018] said that a measles campaign in Sindh is underway and will continue until 27 Oct 2018. Project Director, Expanded Programme on Immunization (EPI), Sindh Dr Zahoor Baloch was also present on this occasion.

Pechuho said the measles drive in Sindh had reached the one-week mark, and teams had done a great job in covering children across Sindh province. She said the total target for the last 7 days was 3.76 million children, out of which 97% (3.65 million children) had been covered across the province. She said the total target for the measles campaign was 7.1 million children, and they were on the way to achieve above 95% of the target, and the 1st week's results were heartening.

"The measles vaccine will help save lives. There have been 122 measles related deaths this year [2018] and this campaign will save children from this deadly disease," she added.

She said: "There are certain areas in Karachi where more attention needs to be paid to increase coverage, especially in Central and West Districts of the city. Deputy Commissioners and DHOs must lead vaccination efforts so that we can get maximum coverage this week."

The health minister said that the campaign would continue until 27 Oct 2018. Pechuho appealed to parents in posh neighborhoods to visit their health care providers and fixed sites and provide this additional dose of the measles vaccine to children so as to save them from this disease.

She said in interior Sindh, all districts had achieved above 95% coverage. Over all in the province, 735 Union Councils [UCs] have more than 95% coverage, and 134 have above 90% coverage. There are a total of 188 union councils with less than 90% coverage, and special attention needs to be paid to these areas.

"The UCs with less than 90% coverage were in North Karachi, North Nazimabad, Gulberg, Gadap, SITE Orangi, Korangi, Shah Faisal, Landhi and some others. I direct the staff to increase their focus on these Union Councils," she added.

She said 11 760 Social Mobilizers were being used to raise awareness about the campaign, and 1408 1st level supervisors, 356 2nd level supervisors, and 1123 AEFI focal persons are ensuring a smooth campaign. Pechuho said major private hospitals, Pakistan Paediatric Association, government departments, NGOs and partners were providing support to the campaign.

[Byline: Fawad Maqsood]

