[This report highlights the importance of checking vaccine status before travel. Even though measles may be eliminated from your home country, you are not protected when you travel unless you are immunized. You also are not protected when an infected individual enters your home country unless you have the full vaccination series.

All the cases reported in this post were preventable had the individuals been vaccinated with the safe and effective MMR vaccine. Perhaps after enough of the anti-vaxxer population experiences serious cases of measles in their children, the resistance will diminish. - Mod.LK]
